CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1776395018
OL,3,CTop civil servant ousted after Foreign
OL,4,COffice overruled Mandelson vetting
OL,6,FShe said: "If the Prime Minister
OL,7,Fdoesn't know what's happening in his
OL,8,Fown office, he shouldn't be in charge
OL,9,Fof our country. He should go."
OL,11,FLiberal Democrat leader Sir Ed Davey
OL,12,Fsaid Sir Keir should have told
OL,13,FParliament "at the earliest
OL,14,Fopportunity" when he learned what had
OL,15,Fhappened earlier this week, rather
OL,16,Fthan having "waited for the media to
OL,17,Fforce the truth out".
OL,19,FThe Green Party and Reform UK have
OL,20,Falso called for Sir Keir to resign.
OL,26,@nD@KOUqD@^O]uD@LOUvD@LO]xD@MOUyD@TO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/10
